{
  "texts": [
    "The results demonstrate that DistillSeq significantly increases the average attack success rate by 93% and generates more effective malicious queries compared to existing methods.",
    "The paper is organized as follows.",
    "In Section 2, we review some essential background information and present our motivation for developing DistillSeq.",
    "Section 3 introduces the design of Dis-tillSeq, including the detailed algorithms for constructing malicious queries and the process of knowledge distillation.",
    "Section 4 evaluates whether DistillSeq achieves its goal of effectively testing LLMs."
  ]
}